overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to ensure all acceptance criteria from the Statement of
  Work and detailed specification were met. The assistant performed an in-depth
  analysis, identifying several critical and medium-priority missing features.
  Subsequently, the assistant systematically addressed each identified gap. This
  included implementing a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness with safety
  warnings, adding sophisticated detection and reporting for complex conditions
  like COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and integrating weighted scoring
  for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness. Furthermore, the CSV export functionality
  was significantly enhanced to capture all questionnaire data, and new
  questions were introduced to screen for pain-related sleep issues and chronic
  fatigue symptoms, complete with tailored recommendations. The data model was
  also extended to include medical and mental health history. The approach
  involved modifying data types, validation schemas, UI components, and report
  generation logic across multiple files, ensuring a robust and feature-complete
  application.
